In a simple form of communication between two people, such as a short dialog, the speaker's utterance and transmission of speech sounds (or speech signal) to the hearer encompass seven phases of speech, namely: <ref>J.C. Catford, ''A Practical Introduction to [[Phonetics]], [[Oxford University Press]], {{ISBN|978-0-19-924635-9}}''</ref> * neurolinguistic programming * neuromuscular phase * organic phase * aerodynamic phase * acoustic phase * neuroreceptive phase * neurolinguistic identification.
